Containerd is a daemon to control runC, built for performance and density. 
Containerd leverages runC's advanced features such as seccomp and user namespace 
support as well as checkpoint and restore for cloning and live migration of containers.

It uses runC to run containers 
according to the OCI specification. Containerd has advanced features 
such as seccomp and user namespace support as well as checkpoint and 
restore for cloning and live migration of containers. 

The code can be found on Github
https://github.com/docker/containerd
